#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:10
msgid "Cuda"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:12
msgid ""
"Different from other packages, ``CudaPackage`` does not represent a build "
"system. Instead its goal is to simplify and unify usage of ``CUDA`` in other "
"packages by providing a `mixin-class <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mixin>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:15
msgid ""
"You can find source for the package at `<https://github.com/spack/spack/blob/"
"develop/lib/spack/spack/build_systems/cuda.py>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:20
msgid "Variants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:22
msgid "This package provides the following variants:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:24
msgid "**cuda**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:26
msgid ""
"This variant is used to enable/disable building with ``CUDA``. The default "
"is disabled (or ``False``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:29
msgid "**cuda_arch**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:31
msgid ""
"This variant supports the optional specification of one or multiple "
"architectures. Valid values are maintained in the ``cuda_arch_values`` "
"property and are the numeric character equivalent of the compute capability "
"version (e.g., '10' for version 1.0). Each provided value affects associated "
"``CUDA`` dependencies and compiler conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:37
msgid ""
"The variant builds both PTX code for the _virtual_ architecture (e.g. "
"``compute_10``) and binary code for the _real_ architecture (e.g. ``sm_10``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:40
msgid ""
"GPUs and their compute capability versions are listed at https://developer."
"nvidia.com/cuda-gpus ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:45
msgid "Conflicts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:47
msgid ""
"Conflicts are used to prevent builds with known bugs or issues. While base "
"``CUDA`` conflicts have been included with this package, you may want to add "
"more for your software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:51
msgid ""
"For example, if your package requires ``cuda_arch`` to be specified when "
"``cuda`` is enabled, you can add the following conflict to your package to "
"terminate such build attempts with a suitable message:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:55
msgid ""
"conflicts(\"cuda_arch=none\", when=\"+cuda\",\n"
"          msg=\"CUDA architecture is required\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:60
msgid ""
"Similarly, if your software does not support all versions of the property, "
"you could add ``conflicts`` to your package for those versions.  For "
"example, suppose your software does not work with CUDA compute capability "
"versions prior to SM 5.0 (``50``).  You can add the following code to "
"display a custom message should a user attempt such a build:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:66
msgid ""
"unsupported_cuda_archs = [\n"
"    \"10\", \"11\", \"12\", \"13\",\n"
"    \"20\", \"21\",\n"
"    \"30\", \"32\", \"35\", \"37\"\n"
"]\n"
"for value in unsupported_cuda_archs:\n"
"    conflicts(f\"cuda_arch={value}\", when=\"+cuda\",\n"
"              msg=f\"CUDA architecture {value} is not supported\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:79
msgid "Methods"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:81
msgid ""
"This package provides one custom helper method, which is used to build "
"standard CUDA compiler flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:84
msgid "**cuda_flags**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:86
msgid ""
"This built-in static method returns a list of command line flags for the "
"chosen ``cuda_arch`` value(s).  The flags are intended to be passed to the "
"CUDA compiler driver (i.e., ``nvcc``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:90
msgid ""
"This method must be explicitly called when you are creating the arguments "
"for your build in order to use the values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:95
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:97
msgid ""
"This helper package can be added to your package by adding it as a base "
"class of your package.  For example, you can add it to your :ref:"
"`CMakePackage <cmakepackage>`-based package as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:101
msgid ""
" class MyCudaPackage(CMakePackage, CudaPackage):\n"
"     ...\n"
"     def cmake_args(self):\n"
"         spec = self.spec\n"
"         args = []\n"
"         ...\n"
"         if spec.satisfies(\"+cuda\"):\n"
"             # Set up the cuda macros needed by the build\n"
"             args.append(\"-DWITH_CUDA=ON\")\n"
"             cuda_arch_list = spec.variants[\"cuda_arch\"].value\n"
"             cuda_arch = cuda_arch_list[0]\n"
"             if cuda_arch != \"none\":\n"
"                 args.append(f\"-DCUDA_FLAGS=-arch=sm_{cuda_arch}\")\n"
"         else:\n"
"             # Ensure build with cuda is disabled\n"
"             args.append(\"-DWITH_CUDA=OFF\")\n"
"         ...\n"
"         return args"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:123
msgid ""
"assuming only the ``WITH_CUDA`` and ``CUDA_FLAGS`` flags are required. You "
"will need to customize options as needed for your build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:126
msgid ""
"This example also illustrates how to check for the ``cuda`` variant using "
"``self.spec`` and how to retrieve the ``cuda_arch`` variant's value, which "
"is a list, using ``self.spec.variants[\"cuda_arch\"].value``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/cudapackage.rst:130
msgid ""
"With over 70 packages using ``CudaPackage`` as of January 2021 there are "
"lots of examples to choose from to get more ideas for using this package."
msgstr ""
